To deploy only tasks and schedules, streaming and Skipper can be disabled by setting the *server.configuration.streamingEnabled*, *skipper.enabled* and *rabbitmq.enabled* parameters to *false*. Here is an example:

```console
server.configuration.batchEnabled=true
server.configuration.streamingEnabled=false
skipper.enabled=false
rabbitmq.enabled=false
```

To deploy only streams, tasks and schedules can be disabled by setting the *server.configuration.batchEnabled* parameter to *false*. Here is an example:

```console
server.configuration.batchEnabled=false
server.configuration.streamingEnabled=true
skipper.enabled=true
rabbitmq.enabled=true
```

> NOTE: Both *server.configuration.batchEnabled* and *server.configuration.streamingEnabled* should not be set to *false* at the same time.
